U.S. assailed for pulling up DPRK over "drug issue" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Foreign Ministry of the DPRK in an answer given today to a question put by KCNA assailed the United States for recently pulling up the DPRK over the "drug issue."
 He said:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As already reported, the U.S. State Department in an "annual report on drug control" released on March 1 asserted that "the DPRK seems to manufacture and smuggle drugs into other countries" and it will "keep tabs on" the DPRK despite the lack of clear evidence. This is a groundless charge and shameless provocation against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The use of drugs and dealing in them, to say nothing of their manufacture, which reduce people to mental cripples, are strictly banned by law under the man-centred socialist system in the DPRK where a sound way of life prevails. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Moreover, there is a strict order whereby even mental stimulants indispensable for the manufacture of medicines and scientific researches can be imported only by the permission of the state. The DPRK exchanges information with the international drug control council and cooperates well with it in this respect. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This time the U.S. faulted the DPRK on the basis of sheer speculation although it admitted that there is no evidence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is prompted by its sinister intention to cavil at the Korean-style socialist system whose vitality is growing stronger day by day and isolate and stifle the DPRK at any cost. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Shortly ago, it slandered the DPRK over "human rights abuse" and this time it fabricated the preposterous "drug issue" in a bid to tarnish the image of the DPRK and isolate it. However, no one will lend an ear to this. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is well advised to clearly know that such a trite trick will only bring to light the futility of its hostile policy towards the DPRK.

Attempts to beautify Japan's history of aggression under fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- The ultra right-wing reactionaries are becoming more undisguised in their moves to beautify the Japanese militarists' history of aggression, deliberately distorting stark historical facts.
 In this regard Minju Joson today says in a signed commentary: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Norota, former director general of the Japanese Defense Agency, in a lecture let loose a spate of outbursts that "the war for greater East Asia put a definite end to the colonial rule in Asia." This goes to prove that he is distorting and denying the history purposefully. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His intention is to evade the responsibility for Japan's past criminal acts of aggression and illegal occupation and rule at any cost and revive Japanese militarism in a bid to realise its old dream of "Greater East Asia Coprosperity Sphere" come what may. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are keen to emerge as the "leader of Asia" as early as possible by launching overseas expansion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Obsessed with this wild ambition, they reverse black and white and seem not to care about their fate. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This clearly shows what an extent the frantic moves of the Japanese reactionaries for militarist overseas expansion have reached. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This also proves that the Japanese political circle is becoming ultra rightist and reactionary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is evidenced by Norota's outbursts.

Great benefits go to women in DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- The presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly recently awarded the title of Labour Hero to Kim Jae Bok, mother of many children.
 Korean women have equal rights with men. mothers, in particular, receive many benefits from the state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the pregnant women enjoy 150 day-maternity leave before and after their childbirth thanks to the popular health care policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this period they monthly receive subsidies equal to a total amount of the basic living allowances paid to them and are given free health care at the relevant hospitals and clinics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A six-hour working day is enforced for those women who have three children under 14 and more. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Special subsidies are given in every month to the mothers of triplets and quadruplets and mothers of four children and more until they graduate from senior middle schools. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first and second national meetings of mothers were held in Pyongyang in November Juche 50 (1961) and September Juche 87 (1998) respectively. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Titles of Labour Hero were awarded to Ri Yong Suk, Kang Kyong Rim, Pak On Jon, Kang Jong Suk and other women who distingnished themselves in bringing up children as dependable builders of the country.

Adherence to theory of seed called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) --Rodong Sinmun today devotes one whole page to an editorial article saying that only when the theory of seed is held fast to, is it possible to bring about radical changes in all the fields of the revolution and construction.
 The article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The theory of seed is a unique idea and theory which clarifies that seed is essential for working miracles and bringing about changes and it is a determining factor of success in all affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such word as seed clarified by leader Kim Jong Il in a unique manner from a new angle means an essential issue in meeting the high creative need of man and a core of the thing making it possible to solve a problem by organically combining all its factors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The theory is an idea of seed revolution through which to bring about radical changes in all the fields by discovering seed and successfully developing and cultivating it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This theory of great creation was propounded by Kim Jong Il while personally leading the revolution in literature and art. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is his immortal historic exploit that he set forth the theory of seed, ushered in golden days in the era of the workers' party and provided humankind with a powerful treasured sword for creation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The theory calls for always attaching importance to seed in working miracles and bringing about changes and holding fast to seed not only in a specific field but in all the fields and domains of the revolution and construction. 
 This theory provides revolutionary principles and scientific methods for creation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It should be applied not in a field but in all the fields and domains and all revolutionaries should consider this theory as a guideline in their struggle and life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The theory of seed also serves as a powerful weapon in socialist construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Fully reflected in it are Korean methods of creation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It calls for conceiving and searching for everything according to specific conditions of Korea to meet the desire of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It indicates scientific methods of achieving greatest successes in terms of quantity and quality in the shortest possible time and most effective ways of ensuring profitability in all work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has been clearly proved in our revolutionary practice that only when the theory of seed is held fast to, is it possible to ensure profitability in socialist construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The theory of seed also serves as a guideline in training people as heroes and heroines for creation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a man-centred theory of creation and change and a most revolutionary theory to transform nature and society by training them to be creative beings with primary consideration given to man. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The theory calls for carrying out creative activities with independent idea and consciousness, creating everything from an innovative viewpoint and bringing about radical changes in an audacious and bold manner. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underscoring the need to speed up the building of a powerful nation by thoroughly embodying the theory in all the fields of the revolution and construction, the article refers to the tasks to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the high pride of the Workers' Party and the people of Korea to have such a powerful means of creation and change as the theory of seed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A bright future is in store for the Korean people who are making a great history of creation and change in the new century holding fast to the theory.

Natural conservation in DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- The DPRK Natural Conservation Union gets its shares in natural conservation of the country. The central committee of the union recently held a plenary meeting and discussed a series of measures related to natural conservation including the issue of carrying out afforestation and forest conservation, river improvement and urban plantation as mass movements this year on a scientific and technological basis.
 The union, founded in November Juche 48 (1959), makes propaganda, education and dissemination of scientific knowledge among masses so as to carry out natural conservation as a mass movement on a scientific and technological basis. The union published scores of books including "history of conservation of Korean nature and environment" vols. 1, 2 and 3 and "encyclopaedia of natural conservation" and many propaganda materials to raise public concern over natural conservation. It also introduced scientific ways of natural conservation into practice to put natural conservation on a scientific and technological basis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The union has more than 10,000 branch organizations throughout the country, which involve 200,000 officials in the field of natural conservation, scientists, technicians, experts, teachers and working people who are highly concerned about natural conservation. It has 11 societies for forestry, plant, land, water, atmospheric protection, hunting, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The societies consist of doctors and professors authoritative in the work of natural conservation. The societies organize regular scientific and technological consultative meetings and public presentation of current materials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The union regularly collects data on the situation of natural conservation in the country and works out plans, thus helping the party and the government work out and implement policies related to natural conservation. It systematically issues its organ "natural conservation" and reference bulletins "information for officials in field of natural conservation." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Admitted into the international union for conservation of nature and natural resources in September Juche 52 (1963),the DPRK Natural Conservation Union has versatile exchanges with natural conservation institutions and organizations and individual figures in more than 50 countries.

Korean women blessed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- Bouavone, vice-chairwoman of the central committee of the Lao Women's Union, who was leading the union delegation which visited the DPRK, said that there are no more proud and happier women in the world than the Korean women who are leading an independent and creative life as the master of the state and society.
 Under the wise guidance of leader Kim Jong Il, the Korean women devote all their wisdom and efforts to building a powerful socialist nation and play a big role in building up the society into a great harmonious family by highly displaying the revolutionary obligation and comradeship, she noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief of the women development centre of Laos who was a member of the delegation said that the Pyongyang Maternity Hospital has sets of up-to-date medical equipment enough to give medical service to women in childbed and babies and that the Korean women are really blessed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Another member of the delegation said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean women are working hard for the prosperity of the country at all posts of socialist construction and blooming as fragrant flowers of families and society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;their happy life is unthinkable without the wise leadership and great loving care of Kim Jong Il who puts them forward and values them much.

Diplomatic relations established between DPRK and Grand Duchy of Luxembourg 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- a joint statement on the establishment of diplomatic relations between the Democratic People's Republic of Korea and the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg was released today.
 The statement reads: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Representatives from the ministries of foreign affairs of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg had talks in Luxembourg on 5 March 2001. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These talks were arranged following the exchange of letters between the ministers of foreign affairs of both countries on the basis of the decision taken by the governments of both countries to acknowledge the independence and sovereignty of each other. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the talks, the two sides agreed to establish diplomatic relations at the level of ambassadors on the basis of the Vienna convention on diplomatic relations and the Vienna convention of consular relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They expressed the hope that the establishment of diplomatic relations between the two countries would enable both countries to develop their bilateral relations more effectively and would provide greater opportunities for exchange on issues of mutual interests and concern.
